name: NonOpioidAnalgesics
title: Non opioid analgesics
description: Originally a clone of the MITRE value set of same name but substantially changed to remove all medications that were not analgesics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This value set contains codes that represent medications with analgesic effects which may be of potential therapeutic benefit in treating chronic pain. It does not include opiate and opioid class medications.),(Data Element Scope: Drug administration, ordering, or delivery),(Inclusion Criteria: RXNORM codes with TTY = SCD or GPCK linked via RxMix to MESH concept Analgesics, Non-Narcotic / id: D018712),(Exclusion Criteria: Opioids included due to sharing ingredients with the Non-Narcotic class)
